author: Reuters Editorial
title: UK officials confident French scallops spat will not recur
description: Britain is confident that France will supply more security resources to ensure that a row over scallops at sea does not happen again, Britain's junior fisheries minister George Eustice told lawmakers on Wednesday.

author: Abdi Sheikh
title: Somali militants kill soldiers, kidnap scores of elders
description: Gunmen from Somalia's Al Shabaab group killed six people including at least four soldiers in the streets of the capital, a day after the Islamist movement kidnapped scores of elders in a central region, officials said.

description: Russia's deputy foreign minister said on Wednesday that the military situation in the Syrian rebel-held province of Idlib would become clearer after a summit in Tehran on Friday, the TASS news agency reported.

author: David Milliken
title: UK economy holding up against Brexit jitters, for now - survey
description: Britain's economy is holding its solid pace of growth, according to a survey which showed the large services sector expanded more strongly than expected in August, but Brexit worries are hitting investment plans and confidence.

title: EU, U.S. trade chiefs to mend ties after Trump tariff detente
description: U.S. and EU trade chiefs will hold a first meeting in Brussels on Monday to pursue closer transatlantic ties after U.S. President Donald Trump agreed to drop his threat of tariffs on EU cars.

author: Nadine Schimroszik
